Will to express certainly

We can use will to talk about what is probably or certain the situation, based on our knowledge or experience.
WE can use will for a present or a future situation.

Present

That will be Sally on the phone. 
(have knowledge that Sally is calling at the time)

She won't be in her office.
(have knowledge that she's elsewhere)

Future

At one o'clock, she'll be at lunch.
(have knowledge she has lunch at that time)

It won't be open on Sunday.
(have knowledge that it closes on a Sunday)

